1
00:00:11,945 --> 00:00:12,785
Go!

2
00:00:12,785 --> 00:00:13,785
Comrades. Go!

3
00:00:21,545 --> 00:00:22,185
Nothing.

4
00:00:22,185 --> 00:00:23,185
There's nothing too.

5
00:00:28,345 --> 00:00:29,345
Ouch!

6
00:00:32,425 --> 00:00:33,425
It's a trap!

7
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:34,825
Take Cover!

8
00:00:47,385 --> 00:00:50,065
Comrade Fah, take everyone to the edge of the forest.

9
00:00:50,745 --> 00:00:51,385
Ouch!

10
00:00:51,385 --> 00:00:52,385
Hurry!

11
00:00:52,825 --> 00:00:54,744
I'll provide cover while you move.

12
00:00:54,745 --> 00:00:55,905
Get back, Comrade.

13
00:00:59,425 --> 00:01:01,185
Hey! Comrade.

14
00:01:01,665 --> 00:01:03,584
Comrade! Damn!

15
00:01:03,585 --> 00:01:04,864
Argh!

16
00:01:04,865 --> 00:01:08,665
Comrade Fah, hurry up!

17
00:01:09,745 --> 00:01:10,305
Go.

18
00:01:10,306 --> 00:01:11,945
Argh!

19
00:01:13,025 --> 00:01:14,624
Argh!

20
00:01:14,625 --> 00:01:16,505
Comrade Fah, how's it going?

21
00:01:17,585 --> 00:01:18,585
I'm OK.

22
00:01:19,985 --> 00:01:22,065
Take our comrades safely back to the base.

23
00:01:22,705 --> 00:01:24,345
No, I'll go with Comrade ploeng.

24
00:01:25,545 --> 00:01:26,545
Go!

25
00:01:28,145 --> 00:01:29,985
Stick to our ideology,

26
00:01:31,185 --> 00:01:32,185
Go!

27
00:01:35,825 --> 00:01:37,225
Get back, Comrade.

28
00:01:37,865 --> 00:01:39,385
Ouch!

29
00:01:54,985 --> 00:01:57,505
Follow them. I'll take care of this.

30
00:01:58,265 --> 00:01:59,265
Go!

31
00:02:09,465 --> 00:02:10,465
Argh!

32
00:04:13,745 --> 00:04:15,865
Why haven’t they returned yet?

33
00:04:16,985 --> 00:04:17,985
They're back.

34
00:04:18,185 --> 00:04:19,385
Our comrades-in-arms are back.

35
00:04:20,745 --> 00:04:22,745
Let’s take care of the wounded comrades. Quick!

36
00:04:29,105 --> 00:04:30,105
Comrade Yue.

37
00:04:34,505 --> 00:04:35,505
Bai Tong.

38
00:04:36,105 --> 00:04:37,105
Bai Tong, calm down.

39
00:04:37,225 --> 00:04:38,744
Where's my dad?

40
00:04:38,745 --> 00:04:39,745
Calm down.

41
00:04:40,785 --> 00:04:42,264
Where's my dad?

42
00:04:42,265 --> 00:04:43,825
Bai Tong, calm down.

43
00:04:44,265 --> 00:04:45,505
Where's Comrade ploeng?

44
00:04:48,505 --> 00:04:50,184
Dad... dad!

45
00:04:50,185 --> 00:04:51,865
Bai Tong, please no.

46
00:04:53,945 --> 00:04:54,985
Where's Comrade ploeng?

47
00:04:55,425 --> 00:04:57,145
- I'll take you there.
- I'll rescue my dad.

48
00:04:58,345 --> 00:05:00,705
- Let me go.
- Bai Tong

49
00:05:02,185 --> 00:05:04,545
I'll rescue my dad.

50
00:05:05,745 --> 00:05:06,745
I'll go too.

51
00:05:07,105 --> 00:05:08,385
Stay here. Don’t mess around.

52
00:05:09,865 --> 00:05:12,024
It's OK, Bai Tong. Relax.

53
00:05:12,025 --> 00:05:13,385
Listen to me, Bai Tong.

54
00:05:27,065 --> 00:05:28,905
Comrade ploeng Comrade ploeng.

55
00:05:29,945 --> 00:05:30,945
Comrade ploeng.

56
00:05:32,745 --> 00:05:33,905
Comrade ploeng.

57
00:05:43,105 --> 00:05:44,025
Dad!

58
00:05:44,026 --> 00:05:46,145
Bai Tong.

59
00:05:46,985 --> 00:05:49,264
Bai Tong, calm down.

60
00:05:49,265 --> 00:05:50,265
Dad!

61
00:05:50,825 --> 00:05:52,305
Dad!

62
00:05:53,585 --> 00:05:55,304
I want to see my dad.

63
00:05:55,305 --> 00:05:56,744
Bai Tong.

64
00:05:56,745 --> 00:05:57,944
Bai Tong, calm down.

65
00:05:57,945 --> 00:06:02,145
No, I want to see my dad.

66
00:06:04,225 --> 00:06:05,824
Bai Tong, please calm down.

67
00:06:05,825 --> 00:06:08,185
It's OK, Bai Tong.

68
00:06:10,425 --> 00:06:11,624
Bai Tong, calm down.

69
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:14,425
No, no!

70
00:06:15,385 --> 00:06:17,185
Bai Tong, listen to me.

71
00:06:18,345 --> 00:06:21,025
I want to see my dad.

72
00:06:21,665 --> 00:06:23,505
Bai Tong, please calm down.

73
00:06:55,585 --> 00:06:57,905
You told me you would take me out of the forest.

74
00:06:59,465 --> 00:07:02,825
Why did you leave me alone like this?

75
00:07:05,345 --> 00:07:06,345
Am I beautiful, dad?

76
00:07:06,705 --> 00:07:07,705
Oh!

77
00:07:08,065 --> 00:07:08,585
Ha ha.

78
00:07:09,065 --> 00:07:10,225
Yes, you really are.

79
00:07:11,505 --> 00:07:12,625
You know...

80
00:07:13,865 --> 00:07:16,425
I and all comrades are tasked with protecting the base.

81
00:07:17,425 --> 00:07:19,385
To make everyone in the base safe and sound.

82
00:07:19,945 --> 00:07:21,465
If we win the battle,

83
00:07:22,945 --> 00:07:25,225
we won't have to hold the gun any longer.

84
00:07:26,545 --> 00:07:29,105
Dad, let's win the battle, and take me out of here.

85
00:07:30,585 --> 00:07:31,585
Ha ha.

86
00:07:32,385 --> 00:07:34,025
Yes sir, my girl.

87
00:08:23,625 --> 00:08:26,105
We don’t need to win.

88
00:08:27,865 --> 00:08:30,545
Just bring my dad back—that’s enough.

89
00:09:19,945 --> 00:09:21,585
You once said,

90
00:09:22,745 --> 00:09:23,785
you don't like the battle-

91
00:09:25,345 --> 00:09:26,345
-because it's brutal.

92
00:09:29,585 --> 00:09:31,105
But what's even more brutal-

93
00:09:32,625 --> 00:09:34,385
-is what comes after.

94
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:39,585
Every time we finnish the battle,

95
00:09:42,585 --> 00:09:43,625
Comrade ploeng.

96
00:09:45,745 --> 00:09:47,745
Comrade ploeng would take me to the battlefield...

97
00:09:49,305 --> 00:09:51,505
to bring all the bodies back to the base.

98
00:09:59,745 --> 00:10:01,545
Comrade ploeng taught me...

99
00:10:04,265 --> 00:10:05,705
we need to bring everyone...

100
00:10:06,785 --> 00:10:08,185
go back to the base no matter what.

101
00:10:14,105 --> 00:10:15,385
It was supposed to be me.

102
00:10:17,785 --> 00:10:19,745
I was supposed to go instead of Comrade ploeng.

103
00:10:23,105 --> 00:10:25,585
So Comrade Bai Tong won't be left alone like this.

104
00:10:30,745 --> 00:10:32,225
What about me?

105
00:10:33,625 --> 00:10:36,265
How can I live if you died?

106
00:10:50,225 --> 00:10:51,225
With me,

107
00:10:52,865 --> 00:10:54,305
you can feel free to cry.

108
00:11:01,265 --> 00:11:03,505
(Sobbing)

109
00:11:09,065 --> 00:11:10,665
It was supposed to be me.

110
00:11:18,545 --> 00:11:19,985
It was supposed to be me.

111
00:11:24,465 --> 00:11:29,025
(Sobbing)

112
00:11:40,145 --> 00:11:41,985
I'm sorry, Comrade ploeng.

113
00:11:44,505 --> 00:11:46,945
I didn’t mean for this to happen.

114
00:11:55,985 --> 00:11:56,985
I'm sorry.

115
00:12:03,265 --> 00:12:05,305
You're so cruel.

116
00:12:05,785 --> 00:12:06,785
Do you know...

117
00:12:08,185 --> 00:12:09,224
Comrade ploeng's daughter

118
00:12:09,225 --> 00:12:11,185
has lost her mom since she was born.

119
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:15,104
Now she's lost her dad.

120
00:12:15,105 --> 00:12:16,705
How can she live?

121
00:12:19,945 --> 00:12:20,945
I didn't want to do.

122
00:12:22,665 --> 00:12:23,865
It's a duty.

123
00:12:52,745 --> 00:12:54,945
(Sobbing)

124
00:13:04,025 --> 00:13:06,145
(Sobbing)

125
00:13:06,945 --> 00:13:08,345
I'm sorry.

126
00:13:11,985 --> 00:13:12,985
Ouch!

127
00:13:16,985 --> 00:13:18,345
There’s a traitor in our base.

128
00:13:19,145 --> 00:13:20,344
Otherwise, there’s no way-

129
00:13:20,345 --> 00:13:22,265
-they could’ve known our battle plan in advance.

130
00:13:23,745 --> 00:13:25,065
Who do you suspect?

131
00:13:28,825 --> 00:13:30,425
Any update on Yaguar I had you follow?

132
00:13:31,025 --> 00:13:32,584
How can Yaguar be a traitor?

133
00:13:32,585 --> 00:13:33,625
He's so naive.

134
00:13:34,865 --> 00:13:36,704
He's been acting strange recently.

135
00:13:36,705 --> 00:13:38,065
Like he has a secret.

136
00:13:39,905 --> 00:13:41,385
People who look innocent like this...

137
00:13:42,145 --> 00:13:43,025
are the real danger.

138
00:13:43,025 --> 00:13:44,025
Untrustworthy.

139
00:13:45,305 --> 00:13:46,745
Especially the student comrades.

140
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:49,945
Why are we suspecting each other?

141
00:13:50,545 --> 00:13:52,345
We can't trust anybody now.

142
00:13:54,345 --> 00:13:55,945
If you find anything, report it at once.

143
00:14:05,905 --> 00:14:08,545
Report Comrade ploeng's situation to the main base.

144
00:14:10,065 --> 00:14:12,065
So they can appoint a new leader.

145
00:14:14,105 --> 00:14:15,945
Comrade ploeng died less than a day ago.

146
00:14:17,345 --> 00:14:18,905
Do you want to talk about a new leader?

147
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:23,065
Sooner or later there will be a new leader, right?

148
00:14:24,865 --> 00:14:26,225
Why drag it out?

149
00:14:50,065 --> 00:14:53,104
Comrade Bai Tong has been crying since morning.

150
00:14:53,105 --> 00:14:54,505
She has stayed in bed all day,

151
00:15:06,945 --> 00:15:09,705
Comrade ploeng is never really gone.

152
00:15:10,905 --> 00:15:13,504
If you miss Comrade ploeng.

153
00:15:13,505 --> 00:15:16,065
He's always in your heart.

154
00:15:19,825 --> 00:15:22,345
If Comrade ploeng sees you crying like this,

155
00:15:23,105 --> 00:15:25,905
he'll be very worried, right?

156
00:15:31,745 --> 00:15:33,465
Dad doesn't like me to cry.

157
00:15:34,865 --> 00:15:36,784
Being Comrade ploeng's daughter should not cry.

158
00:15:36,785 --> 00:15:37,945
Be strong.

159
00:15:38,785 --> 00:15:39,785
Very good.

160
00:15:44,345 --> 00:15:46,585
Let’s go eat.

161
00:16:00,185 --> 00:16:01,785
Since I heard the gunshots,

162
00:16:02,985 --> 00:16:05,305
I realized how close death really is.

163
00:16:08,625 --> 00:16:10,585
Actually, I thought I had braced myself,

164
00:16:11,625 --> 00:16:13,745
But when the incident with Comrade ploeng happened,

165
00:16:16,665 --> 00:16:18,345
I couldn’t keep myself together.

166
00:16:23,225 --> 00:16:26,465
We never know when our turn will come.

167
00:16:28,145 --> 00:16:29,945
Don’t jinx it.

168
00:16:36,345 --> 00:16:37,945
Life is short.

169
00:16:40,585 --> 00:16:42,745
We never know if tomorrow will come.

170
00:16:44,945 --> 00:16:45,945
You and Comrade Ying

171
00:16:45,946 --> 00:16:47,426
seem to have something on your minds.

172
00:16:48,785 --> 00:16:49,945
Let's talk,

173
00:16:51,065 --> 00:16:52,505
So you won't regret later.

174
00:17:04,105 --> 00:17:05,105
Let me help you.

175
00:17:05,505 --> 00:17:05,905
Don't.

176
00:17:05,906 --> 00:17:07,025
Let's eat together.

177
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:09,745
I’ll do the dishes too.

178
00:17:10,865 --> 00:17:12,625
Why are you so strangely kind today?

179
00:17:13,225 --> 00:17:14,225
Mada.

180
00:17:20,505 --> 00:17:22,305
Let’s get back together.

181
00:17:25,985 --> 00:17:29,825
I didn't mean to hurt you back then.

182
00:17:30,505 --> 00:17:32,305
I was really worried about you.

183
00:17:34,865 --> 00:17:36,105
I broke up with you,

184
00:17:37,745 --> 00:17:39,825
Because I didn’t like who I was when I was with you.

185
00:17:44,785 --> 00:17:46,305
Having me as your lover,

186
00:17:47,825 --> 00:17:49,385
is it really that bad?

187
00:17:51,985 --> 00:17:53,825
You did nothing wrong, Sila.

188
00:17:55,945 --> 00:17:57,585
But we were too different.

189
00:17:58,705 --> 00:18:00,464
We can take it slow and adjust.

190
00:18:00,465 --> 00:18:02,224
Whatever you think or feel,

191
00:18:02,225 --> 00:18:04,385
I’ll try to understand.

192
00:18:11,425 --> 00:18:12,985
No need.

193
00:18:14,585 --> 00:18:16,144
I don't want to overthink.

194
00:18:16,145 --> 00:18:17,345
I don't want to be sad.

195
00:18:17,985 --> 00:18:20,025
I don’t want to feel stupid again.

196
00:18:22,345 --> 00:18:23,945
If we go back to being friends,

197
00:18:25,105 --> 00:18:27,025
maybe it’ll be better than this.

198
00:18:39,585 --> 00:18:41,025
If we force it,

199
00:18:43,225 --> 00:18:45,584
we’ll hurt each other without meaning to.

200
00:18:45,585 --> 00:18:47,265
Then we will hate each other.

201
00:18:51,545 --> 00:18:53,225
I don't want to hate you.

202
00:18:56,225 --> 00:18:57,904
Let’s break up while we’re still in love.

203
00:18:57,905 --> 00:18:58,905
That’s for the best.

204
00:19:10,665 --> 00:19:12,745
So long, Comrade Gaun Hin.

205
00:19:45,585 --> 00:19:47,065
If you can turn back time,

206
00:19:48,865 --> 00:19:49,865
would you kill him?

207
00:19:51,905 --> 00:19:53,505
I'll do the same.

208
00:19:56,985 --> 00:19:58,385
I don't want you to die.

209
00:20:01,185 --> 00:20:02,505
Among the Hmong,

210
00:20:03,945 --> 00:20:05,305
they give cockscomb flowers

211
00:20:05,745 --> 00:20:07,185
to someone they’re interested in.

212
00:20:07,985 --> 00:20:09,425
It means.

213
00:20:11,145 --> 00:20:12,265
“I want to get to know you,”

214
00:20:13,305 --> 00:20:14,385
“I want to talk to you.”

215
00:20:23,785 --> 00:20:26,185
I gave it to you. I’m not taking it back.

216
00:20:28,665 --> 00:20:31,025
How can I live if you died?

217
00:20:40,625 --> 00:20:41,825
With me,

218
00:20:43,345 --> 00:20:44,745
you can feel free to cry.

219
00:20:52,585 --> 00:20:54,465
Life is short.

220
00:20:57,065 --> 00:20:59,265
We never know if there's a second chance tomorrow.

221
00:21:17,385 --> 00:21:18,824
I'll go out of the base.

222
00:21:18,825 --> 00:21:20,264
Come with me, Comrade Saeng.

223
00:21:20,265 --> 00:21:21,544
Do we have a mission?

224
00:21:21,545 --> 00:21:22,545
No.

225
00:21:23,145 --> 00:21:24,265
Isn’t it against the rules-

226
00:21:25,425 --> 00:21:26,625
-to go out without one?

227
00:21:29,985 --> 00:21:32,185
Where will we go, Comrade Yue?

228
00:21:33,185 --> 00:21:34,345
Somewhere.

229
00:21:36,585 --> 00:21:38,385
There are some scary legends about that area.

230
00:21:40,065 --> 00:21:41,185
Ghost?

231
00:21:46,785 --> 00:21:47,985
Some people died there.

232
00:21:49,265 --> 00:21:51,425
People die everywhere.

233
00:21:52,705 --> 00:21:54,584
But if it becomes a legend,

234
00:21:54,585 --> 00:21:57,305
it isn't just a normal death.

235
00:22:01,145 --> 00:22:02,465
Years ago,

236
00:22:03,465 --> 00:22:05,345
two male comrades were found to be in love.

237
00:22:07,065 --> 00:22:09,745
So they took their own lives at Chan Siao Cave.

238
00:22:11,665 --> 00:22:13,745
It’s not far from where we’re going.

239
00:22:17,505 --> 00:22:18,665
Over there.

240
00:22:31,145 --> 00:22:32,145
Scared?

241
00:22:37,345 --> 00:22:38,745
I just feel sad.

242
00:22:39,625 --> 00:22:41,545
Comrade Yue, what would you do if it were you?

243
00:22:48,225 --> 00:22:51,305
I’d do anything to be with my love,

244
00:22:53,465 --> 00:22:54,905
but in the end-

245
00:22:55,705 --> 00:22:57,065
-if I must choose between love-

246
00:22:58,185 --> 00:22:59,265
and his life.

247
00:23:02,945 --> 00:23:04,905
I’ll do everything to keep him alive.

248
00:23:07,305 --> 00:23:08,665
Even I must sacrifice my own life.

249
00:23:23,705 --> 00:23:25,265
Comrade Yue, wait for me.

250
00:23:25,825 --> 00:23:27,665
Comrade Yue, wait for me.

251
00:23:31,385 --> 00:23:33,465
Watch your step, follow my footprint.

252
00:23:38,785 --> 00:23:39,785
Are you OK?

253
00:23:57,785 --> 00:23:59,065
I'm thirsty.

254
00:24:02,905 --> 00:24:03,905
I'm really thirsty.

255
00:24:03,906 --> 00:24:04,945
Can I drink your water?

256
00:24:12,945 --> 00:24:14,225
Didn’t you bring your own water?

257
00:24:17,625 --> 00:24:20,265
You rushed me, so I didn’t have time to grab it.

258
00:24:39,905 --> 00:24:42,145
So let's take a break here.

259
00:24:44,425 --> 00:24:46,185
Better?

260
00:25:09,545 --> 00:25:10,545
Wow!

261
00:25:11,145 --> 00:25:12,224
So this is what it’s like. So beautiful-

262
00:25:12,225 --> 00:25:13,825
-it makes people forget their tiredness.

263
00:25:14,545 --> 00:25:15,785
Woohoo!

264
00:25:23,265 --> 00:25:24,905
When I joined the troop in my first year,

265
00:25:26,265 --> 00:25:27,945
I was in a low mental state.

266
00:25:29,865 --> 00:25:31,745
It's Comrade ploeng who brought me here.

267
00:25:33,665 --> 00:25:35,025
He told me to look down there.

268
00:25:37,625 --> 00:25:39,865
He taught me that when your problems feel too big,

269
00:25:42,065 --> 00:25:43,545
if you step back a little,

270
00:25:45,585 --> 00:25:46,745
they’ll seem smaller.

271
00:25:50,465 --> 00:25:53,505
Back then I was living aimlessly.

272
00:25:55,425 --> 00:25:56,505
I volunteered for fighting.

273
00:26:00,305 --> 00:26:02,625
Because I don't have any family members left.

274
00:26:06,225 --> 00:26:07,985
Comrade ploeng told me...

275
00:26:09,145 --> 00:26:11,065
If you don't care about yourself,

276
00:26:12,905 --> 00:26:14,545
then find someone-

277
00:26:16,385 --> 00:26:18,105
-you want to take care of.

278
00:26:21,225 --> 00:26:22,545
Someone

279
00:26:26,105 --> 00:26:27,905
you want to live your life for.

280
00:26:32,865 --> 00:26:34,345
If you find that person,

281
00:26:39,065 --> 00:26:40,185
bring them here.

282
00:26:44,065 --> 00:26:46,545
So you bring me here.

283
00:26:56,945 --> 00:26:59,105
I think you're my person.

284
00:27:11,825 --> 00:27:13,624
My name is Ravin.

285
00:27:13,625 --> 00:27:14,625
Ravin!

286
00:27:15,585 --> 00:27:17,545
The soldiers might hear us.

287
00:27:21,745 --> 00:27:23,105
You brought me a long way.

288
00:27:23,745 --> 00:27:24,785
This place is beautiful.

289
00:27:25,785 --> 00:27:27,624
Why don’t you let yourself go a little?

290
00:27:27,625 --> 00:27:29,185
Try not to worry anything.

291
00:27:31,865 --> 00:27:33,905
This is so damn fun!

292
00:27:40,265 --> 00:27:41,945
My name is Sasin.

293
00:27:44,145 --> 00:27:45,145
Sasin?

294
00:27:45,665 --> 00:27:46,785
Is Sasin your name?

295
00:27:48,305 --> 00:27:50,185
Aren’t you afraid to hear it?

296
00:27:51,305 --> 00:27:52,665
I just brought you up here.

297
00:27:53,705 --> 00:27:55,225
There’s nothing to be afraid of.

298
00:27:58,865 --> 00:28:01,705
I will protect Ravin with my life.

299
00:28:02,745 --> 00:28:05,105
So damn happy!

300
00:28:11,625 --> 00:28:13,905
When will the people from the main base go out again?

301
00:28:16,025 --> 00:28:17,505
No one has been outside-

302
00:28:18,425 --> 00:28:20,065
-since Comrade ploeng died.

303
00:28:20,425 --> 00:28:21,625
There's only Comrade Roong.

304
00:28:22,505 --> 00:28:24,025
She brought medicine to the villagers.

305
00:28:25,145 --> 00:28:26,225
Comrade Roong?

306
00:28:27,025 --> 00:28:28,145
Who's Comrade Roong?

307
00:28:28,905 --> 00:28:30,264
Comrade Roong is-

308
00:28:30,265 --> 00:28:32,865
-the female leader in Saeng Dao Base.

309
00:28:33,345 --> 00:28:35,465
She's the sister of Comrade Fah.

310
00:28:37,225 --> 00:28:38,425
Any news?

311
00:28:39,145 --> 00:28:40,344
Yaguar to me...

312
00:28:40,345 --> 00:28:42,545
They are investigating the traitor in the base,

313
00:28:43,145 --> 00:28:45,745
and who shot Comrade ploeng.

314
00:28:48,385 --> 00:28:49,385
Yang Sue.

315
00:28:50,585 --> 00:28:52,425
I have a task for you.

316
00:29:30,545 --> 00:29:32,185
What are you sitting here thinking about?

317
00:29:38,585 --> 00:29:39,985
I miss Comrade ploeng.

318
00:29:47,145 --> 00:29:49,465
This compass, Comrade ploeng gave it to me.

319
00:29:52,865 --> 00:29:54,345
He was like my father.

320
00:30:00,825 --> 00:30:02,105
I was named by him.

321
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:09,145
Your name is Yue.

322
00:30:09,865 --> 00:30:11,464
I want to know for a long time.

323
00:30:11,465 --> 00:30:13,745
What is the meaning of Yue?

324
00:30:21,265 --> 00:30:23,345
Yue is a Chinese word.

325
00:30:24,625 --> 00:30:25,984
It means the moon.

326
00:30:25,985 --> 00:30:26,985
Write like this.

327
00:30:35,585 --> 00:30:37,705
So what about my name, Ravin.

328
00:30:38,705 --> 00:30:39,985
It means the sun.

329
00:30:41,345 --> 00:30:42,345
How do I write it?

330
00:30:42,865 --> 00:30:44,385
Can you write it?

331
00:30:45,665 --> 00:30:46,665
The sun.

332
00:30:49,065 --> 00:30:50,665
It can be written in Chinese like this.

333
00:30:56,625 --> 00:30:57,665
It pronounces 'rì'

334
00:30:58,225 --> 00:30:59,625
Rì.

335
00:31:04,785 --> 00:31:06,545
Even though the sun and the moon...

336
00:31:08,385 --> 00:31:09,825
are both in the sky,

337
00:31:14,385 --> 00:31:15,865
they can still be next to each other.

338
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:19,585
What if...

339
00:31:22,865 --> 00:31:23,865
I put the sun,

340
00:31:24,265 --> 00:31:25,265
'rì,

341
00:31:25,625 --> 00:31:26,825
right there.

342
00:31:27,305 --> 00:31:28,305
And put Yue-

343
00:31:30,185 --> 00:31:31,305
next to it like this.

344
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:35,745
Does it mean anything?

345
00:31:42,065 --> 00:31:43,065
It does.

346
00:31:44,985 --> 00:31:47,265
If we place “rì” (the sun) and “Yue” (the moon) together.

347
00:31:49,545 --> 00:31:51,544
The sun becomes smaller,

348
00:31:51,545 --> 00:31:55,145
as if it’s being embraced by the moon.

349
00:31:57,225 --> 00:31:58,425
It reads 'Ming'.

350
00:31:58,905 --> 00:31:59,905
Ming?

351
00:32:00,345 --> 00:32:01,345
It means the light.

352
00:32:01,945 --> 00:32:02,945
The light.

353
00:32:04,865 --> 00:32:07,425
So the sun and the moon can be together.

354
00:32:08,185 --> 00:32:09,945
And they shine light for each other.

355
00:32:29,345 --> 00:32:30,865
What’s gotten into you?

356
00:32:31,945 --> 00:32:33,345
You were just smiling a second ago.

357
00:32:36,185 --> 00:32:37,865
Did I said something wrong?

358
00:32:42,505 --> 00:32:43,785
I killed a person,

359
00:32:44,865 --> 00:32:46,345
then fled into the forest.

360
00:32:49,585 --> 00:32:51,265
How can I be your light?

361
00:32:58,185 --> 00:32:59,825
But you didn't intent to do it.

362
00:33:03,505 --> 00:33:06,585
It's still killing.

363
00:33:23,705 --> 00:33:24,865
At first, I thought...

364
00:33:27,905 --> 00:33:29,385
I wanted to kill him.

365
00:33:32,465 --> 00:33:34,425
He's the reason my father died.

366
00:33:38,505 --> 00:33:39,825
But in the end,

367
00:33:43,825 --> 00:33:45,345
When he finally died

368
00:33:49,345 --> 00:33:50,425
it made me hate myself.

369
00:33:55,865 --> 00:33:57,225
I became

370
00:33:58,225 --> 00:33:59,505
another bad person,

371
00:34:00,705 --> 00:34:02,025
who killed someone else's father.

372
00:34:08,905 --> 00:34:10,465
Don't think that way.

373
00:34:10,985 --> 00:34:12,905
There's no need to blame yourself.

374
00:34:13,825 --> 00:34:15,105
Just don't do it again.

375
00:34:34,905 --> 00:34:36,385
I'm not good at comforting people,

376
00:34:37,585 --> 00:34:38,945
but I want to comfort you.

377
00:34:47,265 --> 00:34:48,585
Feel better?

378
00:34:56,305 --> 00:34:57,785
Better.

379
00:34:59,225 --> 00:35:00,705
Better.

380
00:35:01,625 --> 00:35:02,625
Let's take a shower.

381
00:35:04,145 --> 00:35:05,145
Go.

382
00:35:35,105 --> 00:35:36,145
What are you doing?

383
00:35:37,185 --> 00:35:38,984
If you’re wet at night in the forest,

384
00:35:38,985 --> 00:35:40,025
you could freeze to death.

385
00:35:41,665 --> 00:35:43,145
You told me to take a shower.

386
00:35:43,625 --> 00:35:45,545
If I don’t go down there, how do I clean myself?

387
00:35:47,465 --> 00:35:48,865
I’ll wipe you down.

388
00:35:49,865 --> 00:35:51,545
It'll be cleaner than taking a shower.

389
00:36:56,345 --> 00:36:57,385
Hurt?

390
00:37:00,505 --> 00:37:01,505
Not anymore.

391
00:37:24,625 --> 00:37:26,105
What?

392
00:37:36,825 --> 00:37:38,385
Why is your heart pounding?

393
00:37:59,385 --> 00:38:00,985
That’s enough wiping.

394
00:38:06,465 --> 00:38:07,585
How is that enough?

395
00:38:08,425 --> 00:38:10,305
You said it'll be cleaner than taking a shower.

396
00:38:13,745 --> 00:38:14,945
This is only an upper part.

397
00:38:20,305 --> 00:38:21,785
The lower part is...

398
00:38:31,825 --> 00:38:32,865
Why are you taking it off?

399
00:38:50,225 --> 00:38:51,505
Wipe it for me, please.

400
00:39:16,745 --> 00:39:17,745
Are you OK?

401
00:39:22,585 --> 00:39:23,865
What if I'm not?

402
00:39:26,665 --> 00:39:27,905
What should I do?

403
00:39:42,185 --> 00:39:43,345
Do you feel cold?

404
00:39:47,985 --> 00:39:48,985
Getting better?

405
00:39:50,225 --> 00:39:51,225
No.

406
00:39:59,025 --> 00:40:00,025
Getting better?

407
00:40:06,185 --> 00:40:07,505
You’ll get warm soon.

408
00:41:12,865 --> 00:41:13,905
Can I have your knife?

409
00:41:15,985 --> 00:41:18,185
We just got together. You’re already trying to kill me?

410
00:41:18,465 --> 00:41:19,465
Please.

411
00:42:03,385 --> 00:42:04,385
Come on.

412
00:42:07,465 --> 00:42:10,224
This tree will be our witness.

413
00:42:10,225 --> 00:42:12,784
No matter what happens,

414
00:42:12,785 --> 00:42:14,385
we will get through it together.

415
00:42:35,665 --> 00:42:37,184
Why are you giving me a gun?

416
00:42:37,185 --> 00:42:38,585
Do you want me to shoot now?

417
00:42:39,105 --> 00:42:40,145
Look closely.

418
00:42:47,025 --> 00:42:49,345
So you'll feel like I'm always here with you.

419
00:42:51,505 --> 00:42:53,945
I want you to always be right by my side, too.

420
00:42:57,345 --> 00:42:58,905
Here's mine.

421
00:43:06,505 --> 00:43:08,865
Hey! Do you know my last name?

422
00:43:10,665 --> 00:43:12,505
Every student who fled to the forest,

423
00:43:13,225 --> 00:43:15,185
Where they studied, what their names are...

424
00:43:15,465 --> 00:43:16,545
I have all the information.

425
00:43:17,985 --> 00:43:20,185
But you… I’ve remembered since the first day.

426
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:22,464
You remember that well.

427
00:43:22,465 --> 00:43:24,905
Did you have a crush on me the first time we met?

428
00:43:27,265 --> 00:43:28,864
When I first met you,

429
00:43:28,865 --> 00:43:30,504
I thought you were-

430
00:43:30,505 --> 00:43:31,945
-a mischievous kid.

431
00:43:39,425 --> 00:43:40,905
What about now?

432
00:43:42,705 --> 00:43:44,465
How do you feel?

433
00:43:47,745 --> 00:43:48,825
This is how I feel.

434
00:43:49,505 --> 00:43:51,225
What are you doing? I’m blushing.

435
00:43:53,225 --> 00:43:54,225
Do you like it?

436
00:44:15,465 --> 00:44:18,505
Time flies when we're happy.

437
00:44:19,305 --> 00:44:21,265
I won’t be able to be near you when we go back.

438
00:44:23,145 --> 00:44:24,265
Yes, you will, Vin.

439
00:44:28,945 --> 00:44:30,425
What did you call me?

440
00:44:31,345 --> 00:44:32,625
Your nickname is Vin, right?

441
00:44:33,665 --> 00:44:35,505
I heard Comrade Gaun Hin called you with that.

442
00:44:35,825 --> 00:44:37,305
So you won't call me comrade?

443
00:44:39,785 --> 00:44:42,425
Well... we are more than comrades now.

444
00:44:43,185 --> 00:44:45,105
So do we have to call each other something else?

445
00:44:45,865 --> 00:44:46,865
And...

446
00:44:47,785 --> 00:44:49,105
What are we now?

447
00:44:52,105 --> 00:44:53,425
Alright, I’ll stop teasing you.

448
00:44:55,225 --> 00:44:57,065
What do you want me to call you?

449
00:45:00,305 --> 00:45:01,345
Sin is OK.

450
00:45:34,265 --> 00:45:35,625
Someone's here.

451
00:45:40,945 --> 00:45:42,705
A patrol comrade said...

452
00:45:43,345 --> 00:45:44,905
you left the base last night.

453
00:45:46,225 --> 00:45:47,305
Where did you go?

454
00:45:48,945 --> 00:45:49,945
We had some business.

455
00:45:50,385 --> 00:45:51,505
What kind of business?

456
00:45:52,185 --> 00:45:53,185
What's going on?

457
00:45:59,785 --> 00:46:01,505
Comrade Saeng, you go on ahead to the base.

458
00:46:02,065 --> 00:46:03,065
Yes sir.

459
00:46:11,705 --> 00:46:12,705
So?

460
00:46:14,105 --> 00:46:15,185
Yang Sue reported...

461
00:46:16,025 --> 00:46:18,545
there's a rumor about Captain Dan Din among the villagers.

462
00:46:19,745 --> 00:46:20,745
Dan Din?

463
00:46:21,145 --> 00:46:22,105
Word is, Dan Din’s

464
00:46:22,106 --> 00:46:24,944
been moving between the base and the village,

465
00:46:24,945 --> 00:46:26,705
where the villagers gather.

466
00:46:27,545 --> 00:46:29,225
He’s expected to come back again tomorrow.

467
00:46:29,865 --> 00:46:31,184
How is the main base reacting?

468
00:46:31,185 --> 00:46:33,304
We’ve reported it since the day Comrade ploeng died.

469
00:46:33,305 --> 00:46:35,065
But they’ve never sent any orders down here.

470
00:46:37,225 --> 00:46:38,225
Good.

471
00:46:38,905 --> 00:46:39,905
If he comes again,

472
00:46:40,505 --> 00:46:41,745
I'll kill him.

473
00:46:45,545 --> 00:46:46,744
If we kill the son of a high-ranking soldier

474
00:46:46,745 --> 00:46:47,905
outside the battlefield,

475
00:46:49,385 --> 00:46:51,625
that would mean we’re going to war with the authorities.

476
00:46:53,025 --> 00:46:54,344
One more thing,

477
00:46:54,345 --> 00:46:55,984
There's no orders from the main base.

478
00:46:55,985 --> 00:46:57,825
So we shouldn’t act on our own.

479
00:46:59,665 --> 00:47:00,945
The most important thing is...

480
00:47:01,985 --> 00:47:03,865
to avenge for Comrade ploeng.

481
00:47:05,225 --> 00:47:06,465
Whoever is a coward, stay here.

482
00:47:07,465 --> 00:47:08,865
But I'll go.

483
00:47:12,545 --> 00:47:13,545
I'll go with you.

484
00:47:42,945 --> 00:47:43,945
Comrade Yue.

485
00:47:43,946 --> 00:47:45,105
Comrade Yue, are you there?

486
00:47:45,985 --> 00:47:46,985
Yes, I am.

487
00:47:55,505 --> 00:47:57,225
I bring you some food.

488
00:48:03,425 --> 00:48:05,624
What are you doing? Working?

489
00:48:05,625 --> 00:48:06,625
Nope.

490
00:48:07,105 --> 00:48:08,345
I’d better not bother you.

491
00:48:14,905 --> 00:48:17,185
I'll go on the mission with Comrade Fah tomorrow.

492
00:48:20,425 --> 00:48:21,425
You stay here. be good.

493
00:48:24,265 --> 00:48:26,505
What's the mission? Fighting again?

494
00:48:26,985 --> 00:48:27,985
No, not fighting.

495
00:48:28,785 --> 00:48:29,984
Just going down to the village.

496
00:48:29,985 --> 00:48:30,985
I’ll be back soon.

497
00:48:32,825 --> 00:48:33,825
Let's eat first.

498
00:48:35,665 --> 00:48:36,665
So sweet.

499
00:48:38,065 --> 00:48:39,184
What's this?

500
00:48:39,185 --> 00:48:40,185
This is what eating is.

501
00:48:41,905 --> 00:48:43,065
Still not full?

502
00:48:44,985 --> 00:48:45,865
Are you full yet?

503
00:48:45,865 --> 00:48:46,865
I’m full.

504
00:48:48,185 --> 00:48:49,185
I'm not full yet.

505
00:48:53,385 --> 00:48:54,985
Eat your food. Stop kissing me.

506
00:49:33,665 --> 00:49:34,665
Hey!

507
00:49:42,905 --> 00:49:45,344
Get up! I said get up! Get up!

508
00:49:45,345 --> 00:49:46,345
Ouch!

